# .gcloudignore — controls what `gcloud builds submit` uploads as the build
# context. IMPORTANT: when this file exists, gcloud uses it INSTEAD of
# .gitignore.
#
# The ~184 MB model_files/ directory is deliberately EXCLUDED from the upload:
# deploy-matcher.sh syncs the models into the build context from GCS in-cloud
# (see MODELS_GCS in that script), so they don't travel from the laptop on
# every deploy. Keeping the upload to ~1 MB of code makes deploys fast and
# incremental.

# The model weights — pulled from GCS by Cloud Build, not uploaded.
model_files/

# Local-only junk — never needed in the image, safe to keep out of the upload.
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
pytest-cache-files-*/
.DS_Store

# Local sample store and biometric eval DATA stay local (PRD §8). The eval
# *scripts* are kept (the replay job image — eval/Dockerfile.replay — needs
# them); only the biometric/PII data dirs are excluded. They are not referenced
# by the matcher service Dockerfile, so shipping the scripts is inert there.
local_store/
eval/queries/
eval/labels/
eval/local_store/
